# IBEX Harness Shared Package Rules

## packages/logger — the only permitted logger in service code

```go
// FORBIDDEN in services/* and packages/*:
import "log"           // stdlib log
import "log/slog"      // use only inside packages/logger itself
import "fmt"; fmt.Println(...)  // debug output
import "github.com/rs/zerolog"  // no external logger libraries

// REQUIRED:
import "github.com/Rick1330/ibex-harness/packages/logger"
// Obtain via DI from main.go; never create a package-level logger
```

## packages/apierror — all error codes must be registered here

```go
// FORBIDDEN — inline string literals for error codes
return writeError(w, 400, "SOME_ERROR_CODE", "message") // string not in registry

// REQUIRED — all codes from the package
import "github.com/Rick1330/ibex-harness/packages/apierror"
return writeError(w, 400, apierror.ErrCodeInvalidJSON, err.Error())
```

## packages/reqid — request ID must come from here only

```go
// FORBIDDEN — generate request ID anywhere else
requestID := uuid.New().String()   // bypasses the context propagation contract
requestID := r.Header.Get("X-Req") // not validated as UUID

// REQUIRED
requestID, ok := reqid.FromContext(r.Context())
// or in handlers guaranteed to have RequestIDMiddleware:
requestID := reqid.MustFromContext(r.Context())
```

## packages/ratelimit — rate limiting must use the interface

```go
// FORBIDDEN — direct Redis calls for rate limiting outside packages/ratelimit
redisClient.Incr(ctx, fmt.Sprintf("ratelimit:%s:...", orgID))

// REQUIRED — use the Limiter interface
var limiter ratelimit.Limiter = ratelimit.NewRedisSlider(redisClient, cfg)
result, err := limiter.Check(ctx, orgID)
```

## packages/config — all env loading goes through here

```go
// FORBIDDEN — direct os.Getenv in service code
addr := os.Getenv("IBEX_AUTH_ADDR")  // no validation, no default, no documentation

// REQUIRED — typed config struct loaded by packages/config at startup
cfg := config.MustLoad[ProxyConfig]()  // panics with clear message if invalid
```

## packages/telemetry — OTel tracer obtained from here

```go
// FORBIDDEN
tracer := otel.Tracer("proxy")  // global; skips resource attributes

// REQUIRED — tracer from the initialized provider
providers, _ := telemetry.Init(ctx, cfg)
tracer := providers.TracerProvider.Tracer("ibex-proxy")
```

## packages/metrics — all Prometheus metrics registered here

```go
// FORBIDDEN — registration outside the metrics package
var myCounter = prometheus.NewCounter(...)
func init() { prometheus.MustRegister(myCounter) }

// REQUIRED — call the function from packages/metrics
metrics.ProxyRequests.WithLabelValues(route, method, code).Inc()
```

## packages/shutdown — all services use this coordinator

```go
// FORBIDDEN — ad-hoc signal handling in main.go
sigCh := make(chan os.Signal, 1)
signal.Notify(sigCh, syscall.SIGTERM)
<-sigCh
server.Shutdown(context.Background())

// REQUIRED — coordinated shutdown via the package
sd := shutdown.New(cfg.ShutdownTimeout, logger)
sd.Register(func(ctx context.Context) error { return httpServer.Shutdown(ctx) })
sd.Register(func(ctx context.Context) error { return grpcConn.Close() })
if err := sd.Wait(); err != nil { os.Exit(1) }
```
